1
00:01:58,868 --> 00:02:01,746
You're back already?
What about the birthday party?

2
00:02:10,755 --> 00:02:12,423
Da-jeong could've been more patient.

3
00:02:14,092 --> 00:02:15,468
What did you say?

4
00:02:15,552 --> 00:02:17,387
It's not like he wants to be sick.

5
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:18,513
She's not mad at that.

6
00:02:18,596 --> 00:02:21,015
He was running away.

7
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:23,226
He made her say all those hurtful things.

8
00:02:23,309 --> 00:02:26,563
Well, Young-do was just worried
that Da-jeong would have a hard time

9
00:02:26,646 --> 00:02:27,564
because of him.

10
00:02:27,647 --> 00:02:30,650
Even I studied about heart transplants
when I'm not close to him.

11
00:02:31,359 --> 00:02:34,696
He'll always have to take meds,
might need surgery or get sick again.

12
00:02:35,655 --> 00:02:38,032
Do you think
she wasn't aware of this when I was?

13
00:02:38,908 --> 00:02:40,493
She could've hung onto him again.

14
00:02:40,577 --> 00:02:43,413
What's the point of that?
All he wants to do is to run away.

15
00:02:44,789 --> 00:02:46,666
Young-do has always been like that.

16
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:50,170
He can't stand hurting others,
so he'd rather hurt--

17
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:53,882
If sacrificing his life
to help other people is what Mr. Ju does,

18
00:02:53,965 --> 00:02:58,887
making sure everyone has what they need
is what Da-jeong does.

19
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:02,181
She gives up her bed
to a woman who barges in

20
00:03:02,265 --> 00:03:04,142
and opens the door for her when she wants

21
00:03:04,225 --> 00:03:06,185
to get up and leave out of the blue.

22
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:08,813
-Stop it.
-Why should I?

23
00:03:11,441 --> 00:03:14,485
Why did you have to make Mr. Ju move here?
It's your fault.

24
00:03:14,569 --> 00:03:15,945
So you want to play that game?

25
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:18,615
You encouraged her
to date that guy, Choi Jeong-min.

26
00:03:18,698 --> 00:03:21,701
They fell for each other
when Young-do was trying to help her.

27
00:03:21,784 --> 00:03:23,202
So this is all my fault?

28
00:03:24,787 --> 00:03:26,831
-I don't want to talk about this.
-Why not?

29
00:03:27,957 --> 00:03:31,085
He's not the only reason
you're so upset right now.

30
00:03:31,961 --> 00:03:35,214
You've been stressed about Dad's visit,
so you're lashing out at this.

31
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:37,216
Be quiet. Mr. Ju is coming.

32
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:38,343
Young-do is coming.

33
00:03:43,389 --> 00:03:44,933
-Hey. You're here.
-Hey.

34
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:47,185
You're all here.

35
00:03:47,268 --> 00:03:49,812
We were all going to have some coffee.

36
00:03:49,896 --> 00:03:51,731
No, we already had some.

37
00:03:52,774 --> 00:03:54,859
Let's have dinner tomorrow.
Something came up.

38
00:03:54,943 --> 00:03:56,945
-Sure.
-Let's do that then.

39
00:03:57,028 --> 00:03:59,197
Tomorrow it is, then.
It won't change your age.

40
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,406
All right, then.

41
00:04:02,659 --> 00:04:03,826
-Bye.
-Bye.

42
00:04:18,508 --> 00:04:19,509
Mom.

43
00:04:21,135 --> 00:04:22,136
Yes.

44
00:04:25,473 --> 00:04:27,433
Do I have to love someone?

45
00:04:31,729 --> 00:04:32,730
Of course.

46
00:04:33,564 --> 00:04:35,358
Everyone should.

47
00:04:37,443 --> 00:04:38,444
Why?

48
00:04:41,030 --> 00:04:44,742
We need a bigger purpose
than just eating, sleeping,

49
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:48,079
peeing, and pooping.

50
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:54,711
I thought you didn't believe in love.

51
00:05:02,677 --> 00:05:04,470
How could I not?

52
00:05:05,763 --> 00:05:07,098
You're proof that I do.

53
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:09,851
I thought…

54
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:14,397
I was proof that falling in love

55
00:05:15,523 --> 00:05:17,984
with the wrong person
will complicate life.

56
00:05:19,110 --> 00:05:20,486
Like the Little Mermaid.

57
00:05:23,364 --> 00:05:24,532
Who told you that?

58
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:28,369
No matter how awful my relationship was,

59
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:31,748
it still gave me a beautiful gem like you.

60
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:35,793
You are the only proof of that.

61
00:05:46,846 --> 00:05:49,348
If I'm the only proof,
what does that make Tae-jeong?

62
00:05:51,934 --> 00:05:53,144
Well, he's proof

63
00:05:54,645 --> 00:05:57,482
that you should be careful
after daytime drinking.

64
00:05:59,650 --> 00:06:01,611
He's like a life lesson.

65
00:06:05,656 --> 00:06:07,617
I'll tell Tae-jeong what you said.

66
00:06:13,081 --> 00:06:14,332
Go to sleep.

67
00:06:15,249 --> 00:06:16,250
Okay.

68
00:06:23,841 --> 00:06:26,260
EPISODE 13

69
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:32,266
She installed another door.

70
00:06:34,852 --> 00:06:36,729
Gosh. This is nice and sturdy.

71
00:06:41,275 --> 00:06:43,820
Hey, Mun Mi-ran.

72
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:45,321
What brings my in-law here?

73
00:06:45,404 --> 00:06:46,614
In your dreams.

74
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:49,700
I said I'll never let Da-jeong
be your daughter-in-law.

75
00:06:50,952 --> 00:06:52,787
Why are you snooping around here?

76
00:06:54,288 --> 00:06:55,498
This is my building.

77
00:06:57,917 --> 00:06:58,960
My daughter lives here.

78
00:07:03,339 --> 00:07:04,382
Gosh.

79
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:12,390
You look exactly the same.
You haven't aged a bit.

80
00:07:12,473 --> 00:07:16,102
Who are you to judge?
Have you seen yourself in the mirror?

81
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:19,021
Is Da-jeong still sleeping?

82
00:07:19,564 --> 00:07:21,441
Wake her up, so I can say hi.

83
00:07:22,066 --> 00:07:24,402
Keep it down. She just fell asleep.

84
00:07:25,194 --> 00:07:27,530
It's been a while since we last met.
Let me see her.

85
00:07:27,613 --> 00:07:28,656
Hey.

86
00:07:28,739 --> 00:07:31,617
The moment you wake her up,
I'll crack your head open.

87
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:36,831
Come have coffee downstairs.

88
00:07:36,914 --> 00:07:39,792
Who said you could boss me around?
Don't tell me what to do.

89
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:45,756
Back in the day, no tenant would
talk to their building owner this way.

90
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:48,384
This is unheard of.

91
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:51,929
Back in the day,
a rich snob like you would have been

92
00:07:52,013 --> 00:07:53,556
stabbed by someone

93
00:07:53,639 --> 00:07:55,141
and found dead in some alley.

94
00:07:55,683 --> 00:07:58,769
As there were no security cameras then,
the killer would be at large.

95
00:07:58,853 --> 00:08:00,396
So you would be some spirit

96
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,065
roaming around this world
because of an unsettled grudge.

97
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:05,526
How dare you go on a power trip?

98
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:09,030
What did I do so wrong?
I just wanted to see her.

99
00:08:09,113 --> 00:08:12,325
Go look after your own kids.
You skipped Eun-ha's graduation.

100
00:08:12,909 --> 00:08:15,620
You're still on that?
I couldn't be in two places at once.

101
00:08:15,703 --> 00:08:17,997
Heard of cloning?
One for Cheol-do's graduation.

102
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:20,082
Another one for Eun-ha's graduation.

103
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:23,753
Don't ever get fresh with me.
Watch out for your head.

104
00:08:25,838 --> 00:08:27,215
Goodness.

105
00:08:27,715 --> 00:08:29,926
Where's Dr. Ju?

106
00:08:30,009 --> 00:08:30,968
No honorifics?

107
00:08:31,052 --> 00:08:32,094
I own this building.

108
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:33,262
Again,

109
00:08:33,763 --> 00:08:34,597
no honorifics.

110
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:37,058
-Are you a nurse here?
-Yes. What do you want?

111
00:08:42,063 --> 00:08:44,482
My patients must be very upset.

112
00:08:44,565 --> 00:08:46,692
You need to be quiet
at veterinary clinics.

113
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,361
Gosh.

114
00:08:52,615 --> 00:08:53,783
Hello.

115
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:00,748
Over here. Bring me a glass of cold water.

116
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:15,054
Part-timers are
valuable members of our cafe.

117
00:09:15,137 --> 00:09:16,681
Please don't talk down to them.

118
00:09:16,764 --> 00:09:18,307
Where's your boss?

119
00:09:20,142 --> 00:09:22,270
We have the right
to refuse service to anyone.

120
00:09:22,895 --> 00:09:25,273
-Please leave.
-Dad.

121
00:09:26,649 --> 00:09:29,277
-You came to the cafe directly?
-I'm glad you're here.

122
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:32,029
Why is everyone in this building so angry?

123
00:09:32,613 --> 00:09:34,824
What? Who's angry?

124
00:09:37,118 --> 00:09:39,579
You're probably the one
who made them angry.

125
00:09:40,371 --> 00:09:41,581
That's your expertise.

126
00:09:45,459 --> 00:09:48,588
Gather every tenant
from every floor of my building.

127
00:09:48,671 --> 00:09:50,715
That clause is in their contracts, right?

128
00:09:52,341 --> 00:09:53,551
That clause is right here.

129
00:09:53,634 --> 00:09:57,555
"The tenant must agree to be summoned
by the building owner once a year."

130
00:09:57,638 --> 00:10:00,182
"Summoned"? What?
Are you the Genie or what?

131
00:10:01,225 --> 00:10:03,102
A one-million-won fine if I refuse?

132
00:10:03,185 --> 00:10:04,228
It was in the contract?

133
00:10:04,979 --> 00:10:07,565
You should've read it through.
Contracts can be scary.

134
00:10:07,648 --> 00:10:09,609
He'll make you come and go as he wishes.

135
00:10:09,692 --> 00:10:12,445
Do Young-do and Da-jeong
have the same clause?

136
00:10:13,446 --> 00:10:14,322
Yes.

137
00:10:15,364 --> 00:10:16,907
This looks fun. Can I come along?

138
00:10:16,991 --> 00:10:17,867
No.

139
00:10:18,659 --> 00:10:19,785
I can come, right?

140
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:29,712
Did you have lunch?

141
00:10:30,963 --> 00:10:32,006
I did.

142
00:10:32,673 --> 00:10:34,675
-Did you really?
-Yes.

143
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:38,763
I heard you're sick.

144
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:41,641
I'm fine now.

145
00:10:44,435 --> 00:10:46,979
Thank you for coming.
I just wanted to talk.

146
00:10:47,772 --> 00:10:51,817
In Gangneung,
when I told you to stay healthy…

147
00:10:53,944 --> 00:10:55,529
I'm sorry for not telling--

148
00:10:55,613 --> 00:10:57,990
Don't apologize. Stop that.

149
00:10:59,241 --> 00:11:01,369
I was so ignorant.

150
00:11:01,994 --> 00:11:04,872
Everyone can get sick in life.

151
00:11:05,623 --> 00:11:07,667
I made being sick sound like a flaw.

152
00:11:11,921 --> 00:11:12,963
I'm sorry.

153
00:11:14,590 --> 00:11:17,009
I should have told you
about my situation sooner.

154
00:11:19,637 --> 00:11:22,681
We can't always find
the right time for everything in life.

155
00:11:23,808 --> 00:11:25,851
You weren't trying to deceive me.

156
00:11:25,935 --> 00:11:29,021
If we're to blame each other
whenever something like this happens,

157
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:30,731
we'll run out of people to be with.

158
00:11:33,442 --> 00:11:34,610
What about Ms. Kang?

159
00:11:35,945 --> 00:11:37,029
She's fine.

160
00:11:40,616 --> 00:11:42,159
She cried like a little baby.

161
00:11:44,161 --> 00:11:45,871
I've never seen her cry like that.

162
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:53,129
She'd be crazy if she smiled now.
But she cried, which is normal.

163
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:56,215
I'm sure you cried too.

164
00:12:02,304 --> 00:12:05,433
There's this spot that gets
a strong headwind in Gangneung.

165
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:09,603
Your eyes get teary just by being there,

166
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:12,440
so it's perfect for crying.
You might want to check it out.

167
00:12:15,484 --> 00:12:18,988
My bus is leaving soon.
You have your wallet with you, right?

168
00:12:19,071 --> 00:12:20,114
Yes.

169
00:12:20,906 --> 00:12:22,450
I'm not asking for money.

170
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:24,743
Here. Take it.

171
00:12:25,953 --> 00:12:27,580
Keep it in your wallet.

172
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:32,126
And he's alive right now?

173
00:12:32,209 --> 00:12:34,086
JU YOUNG-DO
MAY 10, 1984

174
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:35,337
Why would you ask that?

175
00:12:35,421 --> 00:12:38,007
His life is like a flickering candle.

176
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:40,551
He's caught between life and death.

177
00:12:41,218 --> 00:12:42,928
But the wick's already burned out.

178
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:44,346
But he's alive.

179
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:47,516
When you see him,
just buy him a nice meal.

180
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,726
Don't get too attached.

181
00:12:49,727 --> 00:12:51,896
But what if she's already attached to him?

182
00:12:55,024 --> 00:12:57,401
Hey. She's leaving. See her out for me.

183
00:12:57,485 --> 00:13:00,988
No. Sit back down. Come on. Sit down!

184
00:13:02,114 --> 00:13:03,157
Goodness.

185
00:13:03,949 --> 00:13:06,243
How can I leave after hearing this?

186
00:13:06,327 --> 00:13:09,079
Would you be able to just go home
and get on with your day

187
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:11,790
after hearing your daughter
is going to be heartbroken?

188
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:14,376
Find a way.

189
00:13:17,046 --> 00:13:18,714
-Take good care of yourself.
-Okay.

190
00:13:20,591 --> 00:13:21,634
Take care.

191
00:13:27,389 --> 00:13:32,728
If this guy were born around this time,

192
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:36,982
a black cat would be standing
in front of his candle.

193
00:13:38,025 --> 00:13:41,987
Then no matter how windy it gets,
the flame will not go out.

194
00:13:42,821 --> 00:13:45,783
What if the cat catches on fire?

195
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:49,203
This cat has nine lives.

196
00:13:50,913 --> 00:13:54,291
If anyone asks you
about your time of birth, tell them this.

197
00:13:56,126 --> 00:13:58,963
Now you have nine lives.
I bought them for you.

198
00:14:00,464 --> 00:14:04,385
I lit some candles in a cathedral
and put up a lantern at a temple as well.

199
00:14:04,969 --> 00:14:08,055
If anything, you'll have
more lives than nine, not less.

200
00:14:08,931 --> 00:14:10,182
So it's okay

201
00:14:11,767 --> 00:14:14,478
if you've already used two or three lives.

202
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:19,858
It's been a long time since we last met.

203
00:14:20,526 --> 00:14:22,194
Thank you for sparing your time.

204
00:14:22,278 --> 00:14:23,612
And to celebrate our meeting,

205
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:25,698
let's begin with a round of applause.

206
00:14:27,199 --> 00:14:29,660
Gugu Building!

207
00:14:31,954 --> 00:14:33,914
By the way, who are you?

208
00:14:34,498 --> 00:14:36,834
I'm Young-do's friend.
And Ha-neul's friend as well.

209
00:14:37,918 --> 00:14:39,295
You're Dr. Ju's friend. I see.

210
00:14:39,837 --> 00:14:40,963
What brings you here?

211
00:14:42,047 --> 00:14:44,091
He's running late.
So I'm here in his place.

212
00:14:44,174 --> 00:14:45,175
I'm sorry.

213
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:49,388
-What do you do?
-I work at a TV station.

214
00:14:49,471 --> 00:14:51,307
I'm preparing a dating reality show.

215
00:14:52,224 --> 00:14:54,059
That is a fine project you have.

216
00:14:54,143 --> 00:14:56,395
My daughter is single.
You think you can help her?

217
00:14:56,478 --> 00:14:58,856
-That's enough.
-I didn't even get started.

218
00:14:58,939 --> 00:15:00,524
You rarely go on blind dates.

219
00:15:00,608 --> 00:15:02,902
Why only me?
Am I the only single child you have?

220
00:15:02,985 --> 00:15:04,153
There they go again.

221
00:15:05,654 --> 00:15:08,574
Young-do is here. Come here.

222
00:15:08,657 --> 00:15:11,577
Gosh, Dr. Ju. It's been a while.

223
00:15:11,660 --> 00:15:13,913
-Come have a seat.
-Hello.

224
00:15:14,455 --> 00:15:15,873
You. You can sit here.

225
00:15:15,956 --> 00:15:17,166
What? Okay.

226
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:20,669
You've met Da-jeong, right?
You guys are neighbors.

227
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:22,671
Have you introduced yourselves?

228
00:15:22,755 --> 00:15:24,131
Say hello to each other.

229
00:15:25,925 --> 00:15:28,302
-So a dating reality show?
-That's right.

230
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:37,144
Even the briefest encounters are fate.

231
00:15:37,227 --> 00:15:40,147
So the fact that we're all here together

232
00:15:40,648 --> 00:15:44,234
must mean that
the bond between us is very strong.

233
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:47,655
-Of course, sir.
-That's right.

234
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:49,990
But why didn't you
cast Eun-ha for your TV show?

235
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:52,201
You even cast the vet.

236
00:15:53,035 --> 00:15:54,119
That's enough.

237
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:57,122
That's all you ever say to me.

238
00:15:57,206 --> 00:15:59,083
All you ever talk about is marriage.

239
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:02,461
-Just eat.
-It only took one night

240
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:05,547
for my world to become a minefield.

241
00:16:10,552 --> 00:16:13,097
I'm sorry.
It's been a while since you visited.

242
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:16,225
No wonder
your mom didn't let me wake you up.

243
00:16:16,892 --> 00:16:18,227
Rest up if you're not well.

244
00:16:35,077 --> 00:16:36,954
It's hard to be with him.

245
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:39,790
But at home,

246
00:16:41,166 --> 00:16:43,460
it will be hard because I'm not with him.

247
00:17:01,061 --> 00:17:02,104
Be gentle.

248
00:17:02,187 --> 00:17:04,189
I cranked up the water pressure.

249
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:05,607
-Oh, no.
-Goodness.

250
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:07,317
Goodness! Oh, my!

251
00:17:51,945 --> 00:17:53,572
I don't think he's here today.

252
00:17:55,115 --> 00:17:58,118
Let's pull out
from Choi Jeong-min's studio for now.

253
00:17:58,619 --> 00:18:00,037
Let's keep an eye on Ian Chase.

254
00:18:01,038 --> 00:18:01,955
Okay.

255
00:18:05,459 --> 00:18:06,335
Gosh.

256
00:18:06,418 --> 00:18:08,045
