So I don't want to--

515
00:38:56,042 --> 00:38:57,460
Be quiet!

516
00:38:58,210 --> 00:38:59,253
I'm thinking right now.

517
00:39:08,012 --> 00:39:09,555
You don't know this,

518
00:39:10,473 --> 00:39:11,807
but I'm on your side.

519
00:39:12,933 --> 00:39:16,228
If I wasn't, I would have gone to her
and told her to dump you long ago.

520
00:39:18,230 --> 00:39:19,899
But I owe you my life.

521
00:39:24,695 --> 00:39:27,782
Don't make me a bad friend to Da-jeong.

522
00:39:28,282 --> 00:39:29,992
Can't you just be happy?

523
00:39:32,953 --> 00:39:35,373
I'm having a hard time as it is.
What am I doing here?

524
00:39:35,456 --> 00:39:37,208
How can I be worried about you?

525
00:39:37,708 --> 00:39:39,752
This is so not me!

526
00:39:43,672 --> 00:39:46,467
Must I see my ex-husband becoming…

527
00:39:48,427 --> 00:39:49,637
such a fool?

528
00:40:05,444 --> 00:40:06,821
What do you want to see?

529
00:40:07,405 --> 00:40:09,115
The day before his death?

530
00:40:09,698 --> 00:40:10,699
Or the day of?

531
00:40:18,082 --> 00:40:19,750
We'll talk again after you watch it.

532
00:40:20,501 --> 00:40:22,044
We'll have a lot to talk about.

533
00:40:34,348 --> 00:40:36,725
I know that you sent him to kill me.

534
00:40:38,144 --> 00:40:39,895
I should've taken my time with him.

535
00:40:45,359 --> 00:40:47,653
He was shaken up just like you now.

536
00:40:50,072 --> 00:40:51,198
Kim Myeong-ja.

537
00:40:52,241 --> 00:40:53,909
You think I killed her, right?

538
00:40:56,787 --> 00:40:57,955
Lee Jeong-beom.

539
00:40:59,665 --> 00:41:01,250
You think I killed him, right?

540
00:41:02,126 --> 00:41:02,960
No.

541
00:41:04,044 --> 00:41:06,505
You're responsible for their deaths

542
00:41:08,215 --> 00:41:10,176
because you came to me that day.

543
00:41:11,594 --> 00:41:15,556
MARCH 11, 2003

544
00:41:20,853 --> 00:41:23,522
PURE MURDER

545
00:41:27,485 --> 00:41:28,694
Did you really write that?

546
00:41:42,416 --> 00:41:43,459
Prove it.

547
00:41:57,306 --> 00:41:58,891
Anything can kill you.

548
00:42:00,351 --> 00:42:01,477
A glass of liquor,

549
00:42:02,520 --> 00:42:03,854
or even a sip of Coke.

550
00:42:06,815 --> 00:42:08,567
If you don't kill yourself,

551
00:42:10,903 --> 00:42:13,989
the next body will be found
on the fourth floor of Gugu Building.

552
00:42:44,770 --> 00:42:48,649
MARCH 12, 2003

553
00:42:51,235 --> 00:42:53,654
If he doesn't recognize you
after seeing your face,

554
00:42:54,321 --> 00:42:56,115
tell him you were the nameless twin.

555
00:42:57,324 --> 00:42:58,951
As long as you get the door open,

556
00:43:00,369 --> 00:43:03,205
he'll take care of the rest.
So don't be scared.

557
00:43:16,135 --> 00:43:17,136
This is…

558
00:43:19,513 --> 00:43:21,557
Compared to what I've done for you…

559
00:43:24,101 --> 00:43:25,519
this is nothing.

560
00:43:27,479 --> 00:43:28,522
You know that, right?

561
00:43:30,274 --> 00:43:31,317
Right?

562
00:43:35,154 --> 00:43:36,405
After this,

563
00:43:37,406 --> 00:43:40,075
all those people
who tortured us won't be here anymore.

564
00:43:41,285 --> 00:43:45,331
You can't do anything by yourself yet,
but you have me, so you'll be okay.

565
00:43:47,333 --> 00:43:49,293
Because I'll become a doctor…

566
00:43:52,338 --> 00:43:53,881
and I won't leave you alone.

567
00:44:05,684 --> 00:44:06,935
After this,

568
00:44:07,978 --> 00:44:10,648
all those people
who tortured us won't be here anymore.

569
00:44:11,732 --> 00:44:13,233
This really is the last time.

570
00:44:14,693 --> 00:44:17,863
There won't be any problem
as long as Hwang Jae-sik is gone.

571
00:44:18,781 --> 00:44:21,700
Just finish him and come
to the States. We'll be fine then.

572
00:44:25,162 --> 00:44:28,374
They do it because they think
by crossing the line just this once,

573
00:44:29,208 --> 00:44:31,502
they'll be able to live

574
00:44:32,419 --> 00:44:35,339
normal and stable lives
like everyone else.

575
00:44:48,811 --> 00:44:49,937
Hello.

576
00:44:54,024 --> 00:44:57,194
I remember you.
Weren't you here the other day?

577
00:44:58,445 --> 00:45:00,697
Your son was so adorable
that I remember you.

578
00:45:02,116 --> 00:45:04,827
Right. Do you live around here?

579
00:45:05,828 --> 00:45:07,704
Give it to your boy before it melts.

580
00:45:09,206 --> 00:45:11,792
-Why are you giving me this?
-Today is my last day.

581
00:45:12,418 --> 00:45:15,129
I don't want to charge my last customer.

582
00:45:17,256 --> 00:45:22,010
You know, I've really enjoyed watching
people have ice cream here.

583
00:45:28,058 --> 00:45:31,687
Ice cream isn't much,
but it's something you can't have

584
00:45:32,229 --> 00:45:33,897
when you're too poor or too sad.

585
00:45:34,940 --> 00:45:37,192
If you can have ice cream,

586
00:45:37,276 --> 00:45:39,653
it means that you're happy enough.

587
00:45:48,954 --> 00:45:50,831
MA JEONG-A

588
00:45:55,419 --> 00:45:56,587
Hello.

589
00:45:56,670 --> 00:45:59,173
You've probably watched
the footage by now, right?

590
00:46:00,299 --> 00:46:02,134
If you wrap this up nicely,

591
00:46:02,718 --> 00:46:04,803
you will get what you want.

592
00:46:05,721 --> 00:46:07,222
Don't worry about anything else.

593
00:46:07,306 --> 00:46:09,641
Just cross the line
this once and come back.

594
00:46:10,684 --> 00:46:13,604
Well, then. Good luck with the surgery.

595
00:46:56,063 --> 00:46:59,441
Can you please stop dumping
your friend on the first floor?

596
00:46:59,525 --> 00:47:02,236
As you can see,
he's making our cafe look bad.

597
00:47:03,904 --> 00:47:06,698
-She's talking about me.
-Good for you.

598
00:47:06,782 --> 00:47:08,867
-Ha-neul, say something as well.
-Forget it.

599
00:47:08,951 --> 00:47:11,870
JU YOUNG-DO PSYCHIATRY CLINIC

600
00:47:14,873 --> 00:47:16,792
-Happy…
-Birthday.

601
00:47:22,506 --> 00:47:24,132
Say something to the camera.

602
00:47:24,216 --> 00:47:27,844
Well, we were asked
to do this out of the blue.

603
00:47:27,928 --> 00:47:29,763
I don't know who you are.

604
00:47:30,681 --> 00:47:32,432
-But…
-His name is Ju Young-do.

605
00:47:32,516 --> 00:47:34,851
Okay. Mr. Ju Young-do--

606
00:47:34,935 --> 00:47:36,311
Don't say another man's name.

607
00:47:37,187 --> 00:47:38,647
Okay. I won't. Okay?

608
00:47:38,730 --> 00:47:40,315
I'll tell him to get lost.

609
00:47:40,399 --> 00:47:43,110
Gosh. How is
"get lost" a birthday message?

610
00:47:43,777 --> 00:47:46,488
It's pretty refreshing.
I bet he never got that from a girl.

611
00:47:47,781 --> 00:47:50,284
Right. Thank you. I mean it, but…

612
00:47:52,828 --> 00:47:55,205
Thank you. Happy now?

613
00:47:55,289 --> 00:47:58,584
But can you stop doing this?
You're inconveniencing too many people.

614
00:47:59,167 --> 00:48:02,963
Watching them at your 70th birthday party
will make you tear up. I'm telling you.

615
00:48:03,046 --> 00:48:03,922
Yes!

616
00:48:04,006 --> 00:48:05,799
I need a reaction clip for the party.

617
00:48:06,466 --> 00:48:07,718
Can you stop filming me?

618
00:48:08,302 --> 00:48:10,512
Just let him be. That comes with the job.

619
00:48:10,596 --> 00:48:11,555
I need another drink.

620
00:48:12,139 --> 00:48:14,141
How come that camera never breaks?

621
00:48:14,224 --> 00:48:16,226
That one is pretty tough.

622
00:48:16,310 --> 00:48:18,645
It still works
after filming Seung-won's ugly face.

623
00:48:19,688 --> 00:48:20,606
Hey.

624
00:48:21,773 --> 00:48:24,026
-We're out of beer.
-Great. Stop drinking.

625
00:48:24,693 --> 00:48:26,486
Stopping now would be against the law.

626
00:48:27,613 --> 00:48:30,365
Your Honor,
I did not agree to stop drinking.

627
00:48:30,449 --> 00:48:33,410
Go buy some more.
Get some ice cream on your way back too.

628
00:48:33,493 --> 00:48:36,288
-No, no more. Just go.
-Hey, let us drink some more.

629
00:48:36,371 --> 00:48:37,623
Need anything, Young-do?

630
00:48:38,665 --> 00:48:41,293
I need silence and some alone time.

631
00:48:41,877 --> 00:48:43,170
They're at the convenience store.

632
00:48:43,253 --> 00:48:46,423
I'll go get them. You two,
don't have too much fun without me.

633
00:48:46,506 --> 00:48:48,967
You can badmouth me,
but don't tell each other secrets.

634
00:48:49,051 --> 00:48:50,469
I'll check when I come back.

635
00:48:51,219 --> 00:48:52,888
Gosh. When will he grow up?

636
00:48:56,725 --> 00:48:58,226
I'll go inside and get some rest.

637
00:48:58,310 --> 00:49:00,103
-If you're tired too--
-Young-do.

638
00:49:04,274 --> 00:49:05,233
You're okay, right?

639
00:49:13,742 --> 00:49:14,868
What can I do for you?

640
00:49:28,590 --> 00:49:29,675
What's this?

641
00:49:30,509 --> 00:49:33,220
CHEON SEUNG-WON

642
00:49:50,737 --> 00:49:51,697
Did you watch it?

643
00:49:51,780 --> 00:49:53,532
Why did you send this to me?

644
00:49:53,615 --> 00:49:55,701
Well, I just wanted you
to know how he feels.

645
00:49:56,868 --> 00:50:00,747
I'm trying my best not to punch him.
Should I be worried about him?

646
00:50:01,623 --> 00:50:03,166
Da-jeong will never see this.

647
00:50:03,250 --> 00:50:05,460
I'll delete it right away.

648
00:50:05,544 --> 00:50:07,337
You're so cruel.

649
00:50:07,421 --> 00:50:09,339
I'm not the cruel one here.

650
00:50:10,507 --> 00:50:12,926
You're dead meat
if you send this to Da-jeong.

651
00:50:13,009 --> 00:50:14,136
I mean it.

652
00:50:22,018 --> 00:50:23,854
Ga-yeong will meet us there.

653
00:50:24,354 --> 00:50:25,313
Okay.

654
00:50:39,870 --> 00:50:42,831
We're not spending the night here.
Do we have to set this up?

655
00:50:44,124 --> 00:50:47,419
We can just grab some chairs
and stay in the shade.

656
00:50:47,502 --> 00:50:50,088
That's what we said,
but you wanted to set it up.

657
00:50:50,172 --> 00:50:52,424
That's why I told you not to listen to me.

658
00:50:52,507 --> 00:50:53,675
What do I know?

659
00:50:54,426 --> 00:50:55,969
That's not how you do it.

660
00:50:56,052 --> 00:50:58,305
-You need to fix it on the ground.
-What?

661
00:50:59,097 --> 00:51:00,307
I think it'll be fine.

662
00:51:00,390 --> 00:51:02,809
If it gets windy,
it could end up in Busan.

663
00:51:09,399 --> 00:51:11,067
And there's Youngdo Bridge in Busan.

664
00:51:12,944 --> 00:51:13,945
What did you say?

665
00:51:16,323 --> 00:51:17,365
Nothing.

666
00:51:18,033 --> 00:51:20,160
When will we fix them to the ground?

667
00:51:20,243 --> 00:51:21,453
Untie them now.

668
00:51:45,018 --> 00:51:48,647
Can I talk about Young-do?

669
00:51:50,440 --> 00:51:51,691
I don't want you to.

670
00:51:56,071 --> 00:51:58,698
I wasn't asking for your permission.

671
00:51:59,199 --> 00:52:00,700
-But why not?
-He left.

672
00:52:01,701 --> 00:52:02,869
So it's pointless.

673
00:52:02,953 --> 00:52:05,205
Well, it's not like he wanted to leave.

674
00:52:09,251 --> 00:52:10,877
But I wouldn't know how he feels.

675
00:52:10,961 --> 00:52:14,047
At the end of the day,
he left her because he didn't need her.

676
00:52:14,130 --> 00:52:16,007
If he couldn't live without her,

677
00:52:16,091 --> 00:52:18,844
he would have stayed
even if Da-jeong pushed him away.

678
00:52:20,178 --> 00:52:21,429
That's not why.

679
00:52:23,223 --> 00:52:24,683
Don't say that.

680
00:52:29,563 --> 00:52:31,356
I know that he likes me a lot.

681
00:52:36,278 --> 00:52:39,114
Whenever I looked at him,
he had already been looking at me.

682
00:52:43,743 --> 00:52:45,871
He ran when he came to see me.

683
00:52:48,248 --> 00:52:50,792
When I said I skipped my meal
because I was busy,

684
00:52:50,876 --> 00:52:52,210
he got so upset.

685
00:52:55,630 --> 00:52:59,384
And he always laughed
at my lame jokes like a fool.

686
00:53:01,970 --> 00:53:03,138
But he still left you.

687
00:53:08,351 --> 00:53:12,147
I wonder how someone like that
would have felt when he left me.

688
00:53:12,230 --> 00:53:14,441
That doesn't matter. He still left.

689
00:53:14,524 --> 00:53:16,568
I yelled at him, so he could.

690
00:53:16,651 --> 00:53:18,361
He couldn't do it himself,

691
00:53:18,862 --> 00:53:20,572
so he made you say those things.

692
00:53:22,532 --> 00:53:24,701
That was the only thing
I could do for him.

693
00:53:27,746 --> 00:53:28,872
Because of me…

694
00:53:29,998 --> 00:53:32,751
his heart, of all places, is hurting.

695
00:53:33,960 --> 00:53:36,421
Because I think
that I shouldn't see her anymore,

696
00:53:38,757 --> 00:53:40,759
it feels like a hand has come in here

697
00:53:42,510 --> 00:53:44,930
and squeezed my heart really hard.

698
00:53:53,438 --> 00:53:55,440
The things I went through after moving…

699
00:53:57,692 --> 00:53:59,527
I can't imagine

700
00:54:01,279 --> 00:54:04,240
how hard I would have fallen
if it weren't for him.

701
00:54:09,704 --> 00:54:11,539
He helped me endure all of that

702
00:54:12,248 --> 00:54:14,793
and even helped me pull out
the knife stuck in my throat.

703
00:54:17,045 --> 00:54:20,173
I didn't even get to put a band-aid on him
and that makes me so angry.

704
00:54:23,259 --> 00:54:24,552
And that staying away…

705
00:54:26,721 --> 00:54:29,349
is the only thing I can do for him.

706
00:54:29,432 --> 00:54:32,644
That's not true. You can do
more than that. Be there for him.

707
00:54:33,645 --> 00:54:37,524
Just think of it
as dating a very slow, dense guy.

708
00:54:37,607 --> 00:54:40,443
You can just wait for him, can't you?

709
00:54:42,779 --> 00:54:43,822
I mean,

710
00:54:44,656 --> 00:54:47,659
I'm just suggesting. I'm not pushing you.

711
00:55:05,218 --> 00:55:07,053
We've been friends for 20 years.

712
00:55:08,471 --> 00:55:09,764
But I've been so blind.

713
00:55:12,225 --> 00:55:15,770
I thought I wanted you
to meet a nice guy and be happy.

714
00:55:17,397 --> 00:55:21,067
But I think I wanted you to be happy,
so I could lean on you.

715
00:55:23,111 --> 00:55:24,362
I didn't think

716
00:55:25,655 --> 00:55:28,616
that you liked him that much.

717
00:55:30,702 --> 00:55:31,536
I'm sorry.

718
00:55:54,642 --> 00:55:56,311
Can you drop me off here?

719
00:56:06,738 --> 00:56:07,739
Why?

720
00:56:09,157 --> 00:56:10,992
I just want to sit there for a while.

721
00:56:12,994 --> 00:56:13,953
Why?

722
00:56:15,580 --> 00:56:19,084
Because I miss doing crazy things?

723
00:56:22,003 --> 00:56:23,129
Should I come with you?

724
00:56:23,213 --> 00:56:24,297
No.

725
00:56:25,090 --> 00:56:26,633
Should I wait for you?

726
00:56:26,716 --> 00:56:27,550
No.

727
00:57:01,292 --> 00:57:03,711
That was between us.
Why did you send that without…

728
00:57:06,923 --> 00:57:09,926
I really didn't want her to know that.
You drive me crazy!

729
00:57:10,510 --> 00:57:13,847
Eun-ha kept saying
that you were such a jerk, so…

730
00:57:13,930 --> 00:57:14,889
But I am.

731
00:57:15,932 --> 00:57:16,891
Aren't I?

732
00:57:17,475 --> 00:57:19,853
I was fine being the jerk.
Why did you have to…

733
00:57:19,936 --> 00:57:21,729
Why the hell did you do that?

734
00:57:23,106 --> 00:57:23,982
Young-do.

735
00:57:24,065 --> 00:57:27,152
Eun-ha might not
have shown it to Da-jeong yet.

736
00:57:27,235 --> 00:57:28,194
So…

737
00:57:30,113 --> 00:57:31,156
She did.

738
00:57:44,711 --> 00:57:47,922
Young-do yelled at me,
but I know that he's not mad at me.

739
00:57:48,006 --> 00:57:49,632
He is angry at you.

740
00:57:50,592 --> 00:57:51,468
Really?

741
00:57:52,343 --> 00:57:55,638
That's good then. It's better
to let it out than to suppress his anger.

742
00:57:58,600 --> 00:57:59,642
Gosh.

743
00:58:01,728 --> 00:58:04,481
Don't mind what Seung-won said earlier.

744
00:58:04,564 --> 00:58:06,149
He only said it to side with you.

745
00:58:06,733 --> 00:58:08,193
Everything he said was true.

746
00:58:09,569 --> 00:58:12,363
He's a weirdo,
but you know he speaks the truth.

747
00:58:15,283 --> 00:58:18,870
To be honest, I was quite surprised.

748
00:58:20,371 --> 00:58:24,209
Why were you so mean to Ms. Kang?
You didn't have to be.

749
00:58:28,463 --> 00:58:30,590
That way, I could never go back to her.

750
00:58:32,008 --> 00:58:33,635
I realized that I couldn't

751
00:58:33,718 --> 00:58:36,221
just be a friend to her
because I wanted more.

752
00:58:38,848 --> 00:58:40,433
So you want to go back to her.

753
00:58:44,938 --> 00:58:46,231
How drunk are you?

754
00:58:48,650 --> 00:58:50,652
Pretty drunk.

755
00:58:51,236 --> 00:58:54,197
I won't be able to
remember this talk tomorrow.

756
00:59:07,126 --> 00:59:08,503
I desperately want to

757
00:59:10,004 --> 00:59:11,589
and I miss her like crazy.

758
00:59:14,676 --> 00:59:18,137
Whether it's 10 or 20 years,
I just want to turn back the time.

759
00:59:20,056 --> 00:59:22,934
I don't care that I'd be in pain
and need to have surgery again.

760
00:59:23,017 --> 00:59:24,894
I'll gladly go through all of that again.

761
00:59:27,480 --> 00:59:29,065
I just want to be with her again.

762
00:59:39,033 --> 00:59:40,201
Beer's here!

763
00:59:41,327 --> 00:59:42,412
And the ice cream?

764
00:59:43,121 --> 00:59:45,957
-I forgot.
-Go get it.

765
01:00:13,026 --> 01:00:14,944
I can do it all over again too.

766
01:00:17,280 --> 01:00:20,867
I can get slammed
by a rhino and fall again.

767
01:00:22,493 --> 01:00:23,911
I can do all of that again.

768
01:00:26,414 --> 01:00:29,626
So if this is how you really feel…

769
01:00:30,793 --> 01:00:31,878
If you meant it,

770
01:00:40,053 --> 01:00:41,471
can you come here?

771
01:00:57,612 --> 01:01:00,323
I'm sorry my first instinct
is to hesitate and run away.

772
01:01:01,949 --> 01:01:05,244
I'm sorry for being like that.

773
01:01:06,287 --> 01:01:07,163
But…

774
01:01:08,498 --> 01:01:10,208
I still want to be with you.

775
01:01:12,293 --> 01:01:16,547
Is it okay if I stay in your life?

776
01:01:19,884 --> 01:01:20,843
Yes.

777
01:01:23,971 --> 01:01:27,600
Is it okay if I help you?

778
01:01:32,438 --> 01:01:34,148
I don't know how to do that yet.

779
01:01:37,944 --> 01:01:39,570
Will you do that?

780
01:01:42,615 --> 01:01:43,658
Yes.

781
01:04:02,463 --> 01:04:04,799
"When did you start liking him?"

782
01:04:04,882 --> 01:04:07,301
"Why did you fall so hard for him?"

783
01:04:07,885 --> 01:04:12,306
I wonder if I can answer
those questions like this.

784
01:04:12,890 --> 01:04:18,479
"Maybe it's been a lot longer
than I realize.

785
01:04:18,563 --> 01:04:22,108
Maybe it all started
when that trembling wildflower

786
01:04:22,191 --> 01:04:24,193
met a fence

787
01:04:24,277 --> 01:04:27,238
and was comforted by a small, round candy.

788
01:04:27,321 --> 01:04:29,949
I think that's when

789
01:04:30,032 --> 01:04:32,493
I fell in love with you."

790
01:04:32,577 --> 01:04:36,789
